# Google Sign-In (client-side, Google Identity Services)
# ------------------------------------------------------
# GoodResume signs users in with a PUBLIC OAuth Client ID (no client secret).
# Create one at:
#   https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#   → Create credentials → OAuth client ID → Web application
#   → Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:3000 (and your prod URL)
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and paste your Client ID below.
# When unset, the app runs in a clearly-labeled local demo mode.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Cross-device sync (Vercel-native backend)
# ------------------------------------------------------
# Resumes sync across devices only when BOTH of the following are set. When
# they're absent, the app falls back to local-only storage (per browser) so it
# still works — it just won't sync.
#
# 1) SESSION_SECRET — a long random string used to sign the session cookie.
#    Generate one with:  openssl rand -base64 32
SESSION_SECRET=
#
# 2) A Vercel KV (Upstash Redis) store. Create it in the Vercel dashboard
#    (Storage → Create → Upstash Redis / KV) and connect it to this project;
#    Vercel injects the credentials automatically. Either integration's names
#    work: KV_REST_API_URL / KV_REST_API_TOKEN  (Vercel KV) or
#    UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL / UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN  (Upstash).
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
